Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.front_end.download

Class RecordingRegionDataGatherer

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.front_end.BoardLocalSupport
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.front_end.download.DataGatherer
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.front_end.download.RecordingRegionDataGatherer
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.AutoCloseable
public class RecordingRegionDataGatherer
extends DataGatherer
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
A data gatherer that pulls the data from a recording region. Internally, this accepts requests to store data (after it has been retrieved from SpiNNaker) in parallel and passes them to a worker thread so that only that thread needs to hold a write transaction open.
Author:
Donal Fellows

  • Method Details

    • getRegion

      protected java.util.List<BufferManagerStorage.Region> getRegion​(Placement placement, int index) throws java.io.IOException, ProcessException
      Description copied from class: DataGatherer
      Work out exactly where is going to be downloaded. The elements of the list this method returns will end up directing what calls to storeData(...) are done, and the order in which they are done.

      The recording region memory management scheme effectively requires this to be a list of zero, one or two elements, but the DataGatherer class does not care.

      Specified by:
      getRegion in class DataGatherer
      Parameters:
      placement - The placement information.
      index - The region ID.
      Returns:
      The region descriptors that are the actual download instructions.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - If communication fails.
      ProcessException - If SpiNNaker rejects a message.

    • storeData

      protected void storeData​(BufferManagerStorage.Region r, java.nio.ByteBuffer data)
      Description copied from class: DataGatherer
      Store the data retrieved from a region. Called (at most) once for each element in the list returned by getRegion(...), in order. No guarantee is made about which thread will call this method.
      Specified by:
      storeData in class DataGatherer
      Parameters:
      r - Where the data came from.
      data - The data that was retrieved.
